Desktop Engineering Releases

 

This page catalogues releases from desktop engineering teams. Its content automatically generated every 15 minutes by querying the Github API and scraping Launchpad pages. The data is generated using releasegen.

  • For a release to show here, it must be part of one of the specified Github Teams or Launchpad project groups. Github projects must not be Archived, Launchpad projects are scraped for tags. The latest three releases are shown for each repository.

    For GitHub badges to be shown for your repository, add them in the README.

feat: Add Flutter GitHub actions (#90) Adds some Flutter GitHub actions for easier reuse. ## Composite actions - `detect-local-flutter` - Detects and outputs the locally defined Flutter versions whether they are in the `pubspec.yaml`, `melos.yaml`, `.fvmrc`, or `.tool-versions` (for the Installer) - Useful for matrix testing - `detect-remote-flutter` - Detects and outputs the available remote Flutter versions by latest minor version - Ex. `["3.27.4", "3.29.3", "3.32.8", "3.35.7"]` - `setup` - Sets up FVM, Flutter, and Melos - FVM gets setup regardless of if the repo has FVM, so you can still use `fvm` commands and it will work as if the repo had it originally - Replaces `Atsumi3/actions-setup-fvm`, `kuhnroyal/flutter-fvm-config-action`, `subosito/flutter-action`, and `bluefireteam/melos-action` ## Workflow Call jobs - `flutter.yaml` - For non-melos repos - `flutter-matrix.yaml` - Runs a matrix test using `flutter.yaml` for all locally defined versions, and all versions between the local version and newest remote version - For non-melos repos - `melos.yaml` - `melos-matrix.yaml` - Runs a matrix test using `melos.yaml` for all locally defined versions, and all versions between the local version and newest remote version --- You can find an example of this in action here: https://github.com/ashuntu/flutter-action-test/actions/runs/18766377196 --- UDENG-8310

snapd-desktop-integration

Release/Commit:b8f4e35
DateSep 30, 2025
Fix test build in 25.10 (#155) Some tests fail to build because some NULL parameters were being passed to functions without parameters. By default, GCC presumes that a function declared with `()` has an indeterminate number of parameters, while to specify that it has no parameters it has to be declared with `(void)`. This has been fixed by removing the unneeded NULLs, and also "void" has been added to all the functions without parameters, to ensure that a compile error is always triggered if a parameters is passed to these functions.

If you do not upgrade, all workflow runs using any of the deprecated actions/cache will fail.

Upgrading to the recommended versions will not break your workflows.

feat: Add Flutter GitHub actions (#90) Adds some Flutter GitHub actions for easier reuse. ## Composite actions - `detect-local-flutter` - Detects and outputs the locally defined Flutter versions whether they are in the `pubspec.yaml`, `melos.yaml`, `.fvmrc`, or `.tool-versions` (for the Installer) - Useful for matrix testing - `detect-remote-flutter` - Detects and outputs the available remote Flutter versions by latest minor version - Ex. `["3.27.4", "3.29.3", "3.32.8", "3.35.7"]` - `setup` - Sets up FVM, Flutter, and Melos - FVM gets setup regardless of if the repo has FVM, so you can still use `fvm` commands and it will work as if the repo had it originally - Replaces `Atsumi3/actions-setup-fvm`, `kuhnroyal/flutter-fvm-config-action`, `subosito/flutter-action`, and `bluefireteam/melos-action` ## Workflow Call jobs - `flutter.yaml` - For non-melos repos - `flutter-matrix.yaml` - Runs a matrix test using `flutter.yaml` for all locally defined versions, and all versions between the local version and newest remote version - For non-melos repos - `melos.yaml` - `melos-matrix.yaml` - Runs a matrix test using `melos.yaml` for all locally defined versions, and all versions between the local version and newest remote version --- You can find an example of this in action here: https://github.com/ashuntu/flutter-action-test/actions/runs/18766377196 --- UDENG-8310

snapd-desktop-integration

Release/Commit:b8f4e35
DateSep 30, 2025
Fix test build in 25.10 (#155) Some tests fail to build because some NULL parameters were being passed to functions without parameters. By default, GCC presumes that a function declared with `()` has an indeterminate number of parameters, while to specify that it has no parameters it has to be declared with `(void)`. This has been fixed by removing the unneeded NULLs, and also "void" has been added to all the functions without parameters, to ensure that a compile error is always triggered if a parameters is passed to these functions.

ci: Automatically cancel in-progress workflow runs on push If commits are pushed to the same PR in quick succession, the CI jobs run multiple times in parallel, even though older runs are usually not needed. This change saves some resources by automatically cancelling in-progress workflows on new pushes to the same branch. The implementation is directly from the example of the concurrency keyword: https://docs.github.com/en/actions/reference/workflows-and-actions/workflow-syntax#example-using-concurrency-and-the-default-behavior

feat: Add Flutter GitHub actions (#90) Adds some Flutter GitHub actions for easier reuse. ## Composite actions - `detect-local-flutter` - Detects and outputs the locally defined Flutter versions whether they are in the `pubspec.yaml`, `melos.yaml`, `.fvmrc`, or `.tool-versions` (for the Installer) - Useful for matrix testing - `detect-remote-flutter` - Detects and outputs the available remote Flutter versions by latest minor version - Ex. `["3.27.4", "3.29.3", "3.32.8", "3.35.7"]` - `setup` - Sets up FVM, Flutter, and Melos - FVM gets setup regardless of if the repo has FVM, so you can still use `fvm` commands and it will work as if the repo had it originally - Replaces `Atsumi3/actions-setup-fvm`, `kuhnroyal/flutter-fvm-config-action`, `subosito/flutter-action`, and `bluefireteam/melos-action` ## Workflow Call jobs - `flutter.yaml` - For non-melos repos - `flutter-matrix.yaml` - Runs a matrix test using `flutter.yaml` for all locally defined versions, and all versions between the local version and newest remote version - For non-melos repos - `melos.yaml` - `melos-matrix.yaml` - Runs a matrix test using `melos.yaml` for all locally defined versions, and all versions between the local version and newest remote version --- You can find an example of this in action here: https://github.com/ashuntu/flutter-action-test/actions/runs/18766377196 --- UDENG-8310

snapd-desktop-integration

Release/Commit:b8f4e35
DateSep 30, 2025
Fix test build in 25.10 (#155) Some tests fail to build because some NULL parameters were being passed to functions without parameters. By default, GCC presumes that a function declared with `()` has an indeterminate number of parameters, while to specify that it has no parameters it has to be declared with `(void)`. This has been fixed by removing the unneeded NULLs, and also "void" has been added to all the functions without parameters, to ensure that a compile error is always triggered if a parameters is passed to these functions.
